      "writtenOn": "2026-05-21T15:31:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "My understanding is that the shard-end checkpoint in KCL is a bit different from the periodic record checkpoint: it\u0027s the signal to the scheduler that the shard has been fully processed.\n\nKinesis shards can close when the stream is resharded. When KCL reaches the end of a closed shard, it expects the processor to do a final shard-end checkpoint.\n\nThat checkpoint means: \"I\u0027m done with this shard; you can move on.\"\n\nMaybe manual-ack mode should still do the shard-end checkpoint, but only once we know there are no pending unacked records. If there are pending records at shard end, I think we should probably log/fail loudly rather than silently skip the completion checkpoint?\n\nLet\u0027s discuss",
